## üõ†Ô∏è Installation & Setup

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/johndoe/portfolio.git
   cd portfolio
   ```

2. **Install dependencies**
   ```bash
   npm install
   # or
   yarn install
   ```

3. **Run the development server**
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   # or
   yarn dev
   ```

4. **Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser**

## üìß Setting Up Email Contact Form

1. Create an account at [EmailJS](https://www.emailjs.com/)
2. Set up an email service and create a template
3. Get your Service ID, Template ID, and Public Key
4. Update these values in the `src/components/Contact.tsx` file:
   ```typescript
   const serviceId = 'YOUR_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID';
   const templateId = 'YOUR_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID';
   const publicKey = 'YOUR_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY';
   ```

## üìù Customization

- Update personal information in:
  - `src/app/layout.tsx` (metadata)
  - `src/components/Hero.tsx` (main intro)
  - `src/components/About.tsx` (about section)
  - `src/components/Projects.tsx` (project list)
  - `src/components/Skills.tsx` (skills list)
  - `src/components/Contact.tsx` (contact information)
  - `src/components/Footer.tsx` (footer information)
  
- Add your own profile image to `public/images/profile.jpg`
- Add project screenshots to `public/images/`

## üö¢ Deployment

### Deploy to Vercel (Recommended)

1. Push your code to a GitHub repository
2. Go to [Vercel](https://vercel.com) and sign up/login with GitHub
3. Click "New Project" and select your repository
4. Follow the prompts and deploy
5. Your site will be live at `https://your-project-name.vercel.app`

### Other Deployment Options

- **Netlify**: Connect your GitHub repo to Netlify
- **GitHub Pages**: Use GitHub Actions for build and deployment
- **Custom Server**: Build with `npm run build` and serve the `out` directory

